{
  "stem": "27748.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I totally left out any sort of a personal life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't have one.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't have-- certainly, no Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I had no kind of personal life while I was in the army.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I went back to Chapel Hill in 1955, I believe, and finished the master's.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So at Chapel Hill, I was in a medical sociology training program, where most-- all of us were involved in some kind of ways of bringing social science to bear on the field of health and medicine.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And part of our training was with some psychiatrists-- that is, we jointly did some work with psychiatrists who were in training at the local hospital at the university.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But my particular work was with medical pathologists, physicians who were pathologists.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my doctoral dissertation was a study of pathologists.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the way I did that was I stayed with them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't just interview.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I stayed with them for periods of time from morning to night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In one case, I stayed at the house, and was around the clock with a particular person, really to study how they worked.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so that was my dissertation, was on how these physicians related to other physicians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "For instance a pathologist are sort of the policeman of the medical profession.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They are the ones who discovered mistakes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Did this patient need to die, and so on?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They do the autopsies.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so I was involved in looking at these people, in terms of how they managed their professional careers.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
